Adding error handling & exceptions
wanted no tracebacks for incorrect method args for best user experience
encountered an issue where exceptions were in place but tracebacks were still occouring. 
The traceback shows the exception is being raised in the SDK's HTTP layer:
"File "kiota_http/httpx_request_adapter.py", line 573, in throw_failed_responses"
This suggests the SDK is configured to throw exceptions immediately, bypassing your exception handling.

May add logger for errors?

